## ğŸ´ Stud Poker

No community cards; players get their own cards.

### **4. Seven-Card Stud**

* No blinds (antes instead)
* 7 cards dealt (some face-up, some face-down)
* Best 5-card hand wins

### **5. Five-Card Stud**

* Older, simpler stud game
* Mostly historical / casual play now

---

## ğŸ”„ Draw Poker

Players draw new cards to improve hands.

### **6. Five-Card Draw**

* 5 private cards
* One draw allowed
* Common in home games

### **7. Triple Draw Lowball**

* Try to make the **lowest hand**
* Three drawing rounds
* Advanced strategy

---

## ğŸ”½ Lowball Poker

Lowest hand wins (opposite of normal poker).

### **8. 2-7 Triple Draw**

* Best hand: **7-5-4-3-2**, all different suits
* Straights and flushes count **against** you
* Popular in pro games

